habitat_description:
Typical habitat of this species consists of moist open coniferous forests, oak woodlands, riparian woodland, chaparral, coastal sage scrub, and openly wooded areas where there are rocks or rotting logs. While its primary habitat is rocky canyons with streams and plenty of cover under rocks and logs (St. John 2002). In Washington and Oregon, it occupies the southwestern border of Oregon and in western Klamath County, north into Washington in the Columbia Gorge in the Klickitat and Skamania Counties (Storm and Leonard 1995).

NW	-Shrubland/chaparral, Conifer woodland, Hardwood woodland.
